            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3ESatan's%20primary%20objective%20is%20to%20blind%20our%20eyes%20to%20the%20truth.%20Gaal%20could%20clearly%20see%20people%20attacking%20the%20city%2C%20but%20Zebul%20implied%2C%20%22I%20know%20you%20see%20what%20you%20think%20you%20see%2C%20but%20what%20you%20see%20is%20not%20what%20you%20think!%22%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EHow%20does%20Satan%20work%3F%20He%20tries%20to%20get%20us%20to%20deny%20the%20reality%20of%20what%20we%20see%20about%20sin%20until%20it%20is%20too%20late.%20Once%20the%20deception%20is%20complete%20and%20it%20is%20too%20late%20to%20reverse%20it%2C%20he%20says%20to%20us%2C%20%22Now%20where%20is%20that%20big%20mouth%20of%20yours%3F%20.%20.%20.%20Go%20out%20and%20fight%20them!%22%20(Judges%209%3A38).%20Satan%20will%20mock%20for%20eternity%20those%20in%20hell%20that%20were%20deceived%20by%20him.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EJesus%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20is%20in%20the%20business%20of%20opening%20our%20minds.%20For%20the%20eleven%20disciples%2C%20He%20%22opened%20their%20minds%20to%20understand%22%20the%20Scriptures%20(Luke%2024%3A45).%20When%20Jesus%20opens%20our%20eyes%2C%20we%20begin%20to%20recognize%20the%20dangers%20we%20did%20not%20even%20see%20before.%20%22There%20is%20a%20path%20before%20each%20person%20that%20seems%20right%2C%20but%20it%20ends%20in%20death%22%20(Proverbs%2014%3A12).%20Lord%2C%20give%20us%20eyes%20to%20see!%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
